### Setup fullstack dev server with HTML routes and API endpoints in Bun

Source: https://github.com/oven-sh/bun/blob/main/docs/bundler/fullstack.mdx

Configure Bun.serve() with HTML file imports as routes and define API endpoints with GET/POST handlers. The server automatically bundles HTML, CSS, and JavaScript assets, transpiles TypeScript/JSX, and supports dynamic route parameters. Requires Bun v1.2.3+ for API endpoints and hot reloading.

```typescript
import { serve } from "bun";
import dashboard from "./dashboard.html";
import homepage from "./index.html";

const server = serve({
  routes: {
    "/": homepage,
    "/dashboard": dashboard,
    "/api/users": {
      async GET(req) {
        const users = await sql`SELECT * FROM users`;
        return Response.json(users);
      },
      async POST(req) {
        const { name, email } = await req.json();
        const [user] = await sql`INSERT INTO users (name, email) VALUES (${name}, ${email})`;
        return Response.json(user);
      },
    },
    "/api/users/:id": async req => {
      const { id } = req.params;
      const [user] = await sql`SELECT * FROM users WHERE id = ${id}`;
      return Response.json(user);
    },
  },
  development: true,
});

console.log(`Listening on ${server.url}`);
```

--------------------------------

### Install TailwindCSS and Bun Plugin in Bun

Source: https://github.com/oven-sh/bun/blob/main/docs/bundler/fullstack.mdx

Command to install TailwindCSS and the bun-plugin-tailwind package required for using TailwindCSS utility classes in static routes. This is a prerequisite for configuring the TailwindCSS plugin in bunfig.toml.

```bash
bun add tailwindcss bun-plugin-tailwind
```

--------------------------------

### Configure Bun Tailwind Plugin in bunfig.toml

Source: https://github.com/oven-sh/bun/blob/main/docs/bundler/html-static.mdx

Shows how to activate the installed `bun-plugin-tailwind` by adding it to the `plugins` array under the `[serve.static]` section in your `bunfig.toml` configuration file.

```toml
[serve.static]
plugins = ["bun-plugin-tailwind"]
```

--------------------------------

### Import TailwindCSS in HTML File

Source: https://github.com/oven-sh/bun/blob/main/docs/bundler/fullstack.mdx

HTML snippet showing how to import TailwindCSS stylesheet in the document head. This import enables TailwindCSS utility classes throughout the HTML document when the bun-plugin-tailwind plugin is configured.

```html
<!doctype html>
<html>
  <head>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="tailwindcss" />
  </head>
  <!-- the rest of your HTML... -->
</html>
```

### Fullstack dev server

Source: https://github.com/oven-sh/bun/blob/main/docs/bundler/fullstack.mdx

To get started with Bun's fullstack dev server, you import HTML files and pass them to the `routes` option in `Bun.serve()`. This allows Bun to bundle and route HTML files, such as `index.html` to "/" and `dashboard.html` to "/dashboard". Bun's server uses `HTMLRewriter` to scan the HTML for `<script>` and `<link>` tags, runs Bun's JavaScript & CSS bundler on them, transpiles any TypeScript, JSX, and TSX, downlevels CSS with Bun's CSS parser, and then serves the result. Additionally, `Bun.serve()` can handle API endpoints, allowing you to define `GET` and `POST` methods for routes like `/api/users` and dynamic routes like `/api/users/:id` directly within the server configuration. This integrated approach simplifies building fullstack applications by combining frontend asset bundling and backend API handling.

